Check this code snippet

``` rust
extern crate mio;

fn main() {
    println!("HELLO?");

    // This should be `mio::tcp::TcpListener`, but rustc insisted that it is `std::net::tcp::TcpListener`
    let listener = mio::tcp::TcpListener::bind("127.0.0.1:1080").unwrap();

    match listener.accept() {
        Ok(None) => {
            println!("WOULDBLOCK");
        },
        Ok(Some(stream)) => {
            println!("Got stream");
        },
        Err(err) => {
            println!("Err {:?}", err);
        }
    }
}
```

In this code snippet should be `mio::tcp::TcpListener`, but rustc insisted that it should be `std::net::tcp::TcpListener`.

